/** \defgroup ViewDatatypes Datatypes for the VIEW framework
		\ingroup Visualisation
		In this section the color datatypes and their help classes are defined.
*/

/**     \defgroup ViewDatatypeColors Different color classes
				\ingroup ViewDatatypes
				There are the two different color classes in VIEW.
				The class \link BALL::VIEW::ColorRGBA ColorRGBA \endlink uses the RGBA parameter to define a
				color. Because of the conversion class \link BALL::VIEW::ColorUnit ColorUnit \endlink different
				types of input parameter are possible.
				The class \link BALL::VIEW::ColorHSV ColorHSV \endlink uses the HSV parameter to define a
				color. It uses the class \link BALL::VIEW::ColorUnit ColorUnit \endlink for the <em>S</em> and <em>V</em> component.
				These two components as all RGBA components are of range <em>0 - 255</em>.
				The <em>H</em> component however is of range <em>0 - 360</em>. Therefore
				the class \link BALL::VIEW::ColorUnitHue ColorUnitHue \endlink is used for different types of input
				parameter.
 */

/**     \defgroup ViewDatatypeFormat Format conversion classes used by the color classes
				\ingroup ViewDatatypes
				These two classes are used by \link BALL::VIEW::ColorRGBA ColorRGBA \endlink and 
				\link BALL::VIEW::ColorHSV ColorHSV\endlink . They allow them to use different types of input parameters 
				like integers, floats or even strings (numbers in hex format).
 */


